propertyObj.description:
Contains the Integration Flow address which will be triggered during the execution of the Pre-Exit Integration Flow Step.  

For Example:   
/generic_pre_exit_process_direct

Contains the Integration Flow address which will be triggered during the execution of the Post-Exit Integration Flow Step.  

For Example:   
/generic_post_exit_process_direct

Indicates whether a custom Customer Pre-Exit Flow is enabled. If this is enabled the “CustomerPreExitFlow” Receiver must be configured.
Valid values: true/false

Represents the SAP S/4HANA Cloud Plant ID.  

The Plant is mandatory and used to filter stock availability results to reflect an inventory, enabling better resource planning.  
  
For Example:  

3810  
1010

The storage location provides a detailed level of inventory management and control within a plant.   

Multiple values can be listed by using commas for delimiter  

  

For Example:  

381A  
101A  
381A, 381B

The BigCommerce Location ID represents the BigCommerce Location in which SAP S/4HANA Stock will be replicated.  

For Example:  
64685080687  
68676845679  
68744249455

Indicates whether a custom Customer Post-Exit Flow is enabled. If this is enabled the “CustomerPostExitFlow” Receiver must be configured.
Valid values: true/false

It Indicates whether logging of System Payloads is enabled. This is not recommended to be enabled in a live environment unless necessary.  

Valid values:  

true  
false

Indicates whether logging of Exceptions, as attachments, is enabled. 

 

Default Value: true 

 

Valid values: 

true 

false

Specify the SAP S/4HANA Cloud API Base URL 

 

For Example: 

https://xxxxxxx-api.s4hana.cloud.sap/

The type of proxy you want to use for establishing connection with the OData V2 service.

Default value: Internet
Authentication method that you want to use for connecting to the OData V2 service.
Specify the name of the deployed User Credentials Security Material that holds the username and password used to authenticate with SAP S/4HANA Cloud

Keep this option selected (default setting). It ensures that your integration flow is protected against Cross-Site-Request-Forgery, a kind of attack where a malicious party can perform harmful actions by masquerading as the logged in user.
Enable this option to reuse connection objects from the internal connection pool which in turn improves the network turnaround time for multiple communications to a same end point.
The resource path to connect to the OData service
Maximum time system waits before operation is terminated
Specify the name of the deployed Secure Parameter that holds the access token used to authorize with BigCommerce
Triggers integration flows based on a predefined schedule

Configure the session handling scope for HTTP based endpoints
Options:
None - Switched off
On Exchange - Each exchange corresponds to a single session
On Integration Flow - Only one session will be used across the whole integration flow
It is visible only when On-Premise is selected for Proxy type. Used to connect Cloud SAP Connector with your account.

Your BigCommerce base URL. The store hash part can be extracted from the BigCommerce dashboard URL: https://store-XXXXXX.mybigcommerce.com/manage/dashboard 

  

Example of a valid value:  

https://api.bigcommerce.com/stores/abcdef1234

propertyObj.key: BigCommerce Attach Error Details on Failure
propertyObj.description:
If selected, any errors encountered by the adapter will be output in a separate text attachment



Default value: True

Specify the accepted response headers. Use a pipe “|”-separated list. Using “*” will accept all response headers

Default value: *
Represents the number of BigCommerce Products that will be retrieved in each query to BigCommerce  during the execution of the Integration Flow.
